# GymBro API — Documentation System

Before any backend task, read the one authoritative doc that owns your topic. **System facts live in the
root `docs/` SSOT** (routed by [`../../../docs/README.md`](../../../docs/README.md)); backend layout/build/
patterns live in [`../../docs/BACKEND.md`](../../docs/BACKEND.md); conventions in the repo-root `CLAUDE.md`.

| What you need | Read |
|---|---|
| Big picture, stack, run, risks | `../../../docs/SYSTEM_OVERVIEW.md` |
| Module boundaries, endpoints, dependencies | `../../../docs/MODULES.md` |
| Domain entities, EF filters, tenancy | `../../../docs/DATABASE.md` |
| Authorization, roles, permission matrix, tenant isolation | `../../../docs/PERMISSIONS.md` |
| Lifecycle rules (plan/assignment/session/membership) | `../../../docs/BUSINESS_RULES.md` |
| End-to-end flows (onboarding, invites, sessions) | `../../../docs/USER_FLOWS.md` |
