| Solution layout, build/run/migrate, add-a-feature | `../../docs/BACKEND.md` |

## Key conventions

- All handlers return `Result`/`Result<T>` — never throw for business rules
- Controllers only map `Error.Code` → HTTP status codes (thin controllers)
- EF global filters: tenant isolation + soft-delete (admin bypasses both)
- `X-Tenant-Id` required for tenant-scoped calls; read via `ICurrentUser`/`ITenantContext`, never raw
- FluentValidation validators live beside their command files
- MediatR pipeline (order): `ValidationBehavior` → `AuthorizationBehavior` → `PlatformAdminBehavior`
- Namespaces: `Modules.<Module>Module.<Layer>.<Subfolder>` (folders are `Modules.X`)
- DTO mapping: explicit only in `Application/Mapping/<Module>Mapping.cs` (see repo root `CLAUDE.md`)

## Update rules (MANDATORY)

When behavior changes, update the **one** root `docs/*` file that owns that fact (see `../../../docs/README.md`):

- New/changed endpoint or module dependency → `MODULES.md`
- New entity / field / EF filter → `DATABASE.md`
- Permission or tenant-isolation change → `PERMISSIONS.md`
- Lifecycle rule (plan/assignment/session/membership) → `BUSINESS_RULES.md`
- Flow change (onboarding, invite, session) → `USER_FLOWS.md`
- Token lifecycle change → `REFRESH_TOKEN_DESIGN.md`

Do not duplicate a fact across docs; link instead.
